<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species frequently occurred in the field. Plants affected by this species are 
<taxonomicName genus="Tritium" lsidName="Tritium aestivum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aestivum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tritium aestivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(wheat), 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Oryza" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oryza sativa" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Oryza sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(rice), 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sacharum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sacharum officinarium" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinarium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sacharum officinarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sugarcane), and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Echinochloa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Echinochloa colonum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colonum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Echinochloa colonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(jungle rice). This species is hemimetabolous and moults 8-11 times to become adult (pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Global distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Ukraine, France, Spain, USA, India, West Bengal, Kashmir, Pakistan, Mali (
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, MM" journalOrPublisher="The Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" refId="B6" refString="Cigliano, MM, Braun, H, Eades, DC, Otte, D, 2020. Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0/5.0. http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" title="Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0 / 5.0." url="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" year="2020">Cigliano et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Geer" authorityYear="1773" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Gryllus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gryllus bimaculatus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gryllus bimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is variable in size with colour variations. During this study we collected this species from dry parts of Nagarparkar and confirm its presence in dry barren areas. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard, L" journalOrPublisher="The Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 421" refId="B5" refString="Chopard, L, 1969. The fauna of India and adjacent countries like Orthoptera: Gryllidae. The Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta 2: 1 - 421" title="The fauna of India and adjacent countries like Orthoptera: Gryllidae." volume="2" year="1969">Chopard (1969)</bibRefCitation>
reported that 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. (Gryllus) bimaculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bimaculatus" subGenus="Gryllus">G. (Gryllus) bimaculatus</taxonomicName>
causes severe damage to potato plants.
</paragraph>
